    "explanation": "The major product(s) obtained in the given reaction are<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8hwebdw/ab57fa5b-1b51-4283-b487-a48b530c4cf3/5e490e40-3d1f-11ed-8a57-433cdd4ead62/file-1l8hwebdx.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8hwebdw/ab57fa5b-1b51-4283-b487-a48b530c4cf3/5e490e40-3d1f-11ed-8a57-433cdd4ead62/file-1l8hwebdx.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2018 Chemistry - Isomerism Question 10 English Explanation 1\"><br>The mechanism for the above given reaction is as follows. When the $$\\pi$$-electrons of the alkene approach a molecule of Br<sub>2</sub>, one of the bromine atoms accepts them and releases the shared electrons to the other bromine atom. A cyclic bromonium ion is formed.<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8hwdxpc/3114f35c-e5ba-4ee1-88e7-2a6cb0de13c5/53b75e00-3d1f-11ed-8a57-433cdd4ead62/file-1l8hwdxpd.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8hwdxpc/3114f35c-e5ba-4ee1-88e7-2a6cb0de13c5/53b75e00-3d1f-11ed-8a57-433cdd4ead62/file-1l8hwdxpd.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2018 Chemistry - Isomerism Question 10 English Explanation 2\"><br>In next step, Br<sup>$$-$$</sup> attacks a carbon atom of the bromonium ion. This release the strain in the three-membered ring and form a vicinal dibromide.<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8hwdgf8/d938c108-9431-44bc-a9ee-a8e0d40558ee/465e0240-3d1f-11ed-8a57-433cdd4ead62/file-1l8hwdgf9.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8hwdgf8/d938c108-9431-44bc-a9ee-a8e0d40558ee/465e0240-3d1f-11ed-8a57-433cdd4ead62/file-1l8hwdgf9.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2018 Chemistry - Isomerism Question 10 English Explanation 3\">",
