    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "(a) These are cis and trans isomers not enantiomers (Thus, false).<br><br>(b) CH<sub>3</sub>CHO on reaction with HCN gives racemic mixture of cyanohydrin (Thus, true).<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m5ampj7m/1e6320b2-7db5-41e4-8dfe-8b512ba97065/21e5c620-c673-11ef-95a8-2787fde10bdd/file-jaoe38c1m5ampj7n.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m5ampj7m/1e6320b2-7db5-41e4-8dfe-8b512ba97065/21e5c620-c673-11ef-95a8-2787fde10bdd/file-jaoe38c1m5ampj7n.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"WB JEE 2016 Chemistry - Isomerism Question 9 English Explanation 1\"><br><br>(c) <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m5ampgzg/5476197d-73d4-4970-a680-1cf7ac7a7f4c/202d67c0-c673-11ef-95a8-2787fde10bdd/file-jaoe38c1m5ampgzh.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m5ampgzg/5476197d-73d4-4970-a680-1cf7ac7a7f4c/202d67c0-c673-11ef-95a8-2787fde10bdd/file-jaoe38c1m5ampgzh.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"WB JEE 2016 Chemistry - Isomerism Question 9 English Explanation 2\"><br><br>(i) and (ii) both have R-configuration thus, are not enantiomers.<br><br>(d) CH<sub>3</sub> $$-$$ CH $$=$$ NOH shows geometrical isomers.<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m5ampeng/853b21fe-d742-4472-b23f-f36ccbc38232/1e5ffac0-c673-11ef-95a8-2787fde10bdd/file-jaoe38c1m5ampenh.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m5ampeng/853b21fe-d742-4472-b23f-f36ccbc38232/1e5ffac0-c673-11ef-95a8-2787fde10bdd/file-jaoe38c1m5ampenh.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"WB JEE 2