      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The given conformers of n-butane are</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ldb26vgt/1acc6142-676b-4bac-b17f-850df4d623d7/9e72a7d0-9c59-11ed-9319-f1181e85fdb4/file-1ldb26vgu.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ldb26vgt/1acc6142-676b-4bac-b17f-850df4d623d7/9e72a7d0-9c59-11ed-9319-f1181e85fdb4/file-1ldb26vgu.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2022 Chemistry - Isomerism Question 7 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Staggered form is the most stable form as bulky methyl group are at 180$$^\\circ$$ from each other and hence have minimum angular strain. While gauche from (I and III) are less stable form as bulky methyl group are closer.</p>\n<p>Hence, the order of stability is</p>\n<p>II &gt; I = III</p>",
